    rating: "Pretty Good"
    comments: "The jokes were actually pretty funny and back to his old self as his script really was not taking itself too seriously as it was in McKay\'s previous two movies (standout joke being the non-sequiturs to the General asking for money for the snacks; it is pretty obvious at how the movie tries to force politics into its message, its just extremely overt and not well carried out cause of how overt it is)"
