  plot_structure: "Plot Structure was a bit of the mess (there are really two climaxes (and while the movie does a good job heading into the first one, it becomes a huge mess after the this as it goes to the end))"
  pacing: "No consistent pace at all in the movie (some parts felt slow and some parts felt really fast)"
  climax: "Build to the climax (or two climaxes) is done well as the real climax is more built off of the suspense coming down with the characters\' having their realizations"
  final_notes: "The forced political message of the movie really makes it a mess as the inconsistent structure and very simple showing of this message really hurts at what the movie is trying to show"
  overall: "Overall, it is great to see Adam McKay play more to his roots at not taking himself too seriously as he creates a funny comedy that has some real highlights, though he still has a big mess on his hands from a pretty poorly structured plot and forced political message that is not told well"
